<p>I went ahead and updated the 'warning box'. The background image was a link that pointed at something <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1519153768" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;">djkaktus</a></span> hosted a long time ago, but is no longer there; I replaced it with an image that closely mimics (to the best of my memory) what it was (a mostly-transparent SCP logo).</p>
<p>I'm also going to go back into my old skips and make the correction &#8212; I'd suggest anyone who uses this formating do the same. Either use the URL I provided (it links to a file on my author page, which I won't be deleting any time soon), or download the file and upload it to your page to use it. Here's a <a href="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/the-great-hippo/scp_trans.png">link</a> to the background *.png in question!</p>

